    "summary": {
        "biotoolsCURIE": "biotools:motus",
        "biotoolsID": "motus",
        "description": "Metagenomic operational taxonomic units (mOTUs) allow for the taxonomic profiling of known (sequenced) and unknown microorganisms at species-level resolution from shotgun sequencing data. The method clusters single-copy phylogenetic marker gene sequences from metagenomes and reference genomes into mOTUs to quantify their abundances in shotgun metagenomic samples.",
